<paragraph blockId="5.[900,1367,367,388]" box="[900,1367,367,388]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<heading box="[900,1367,367,388]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="4">
GENUS: 
<taxonomicName authority="Pan &amp; Lin &amp; Gong &amp; Al-Rashied &amp; Song, 2012" authorityName="Pan &amp; Lin &amp; Gong &amp; Al-Rashied &amp; Song" authorityYear="2012" box="[996,1237,367,388]" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Hartmannulidae" genus="Aporthotrochilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus" status="GEN. NOV.">APORTHOTROCHILIA</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1247,1367,367,388]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1247,1367,367,388]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="genus">GEN. NOV.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[826,1441,405,580]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis box="[826,945,406,427]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Dorsoventrally compressed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="POCHE" authorityYear="1913" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Hartmannulidae" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="family">Hartmannulidae</taxonomicName>
with a podite; oral kineties reduced to two fragments; several kinetal fragments positioned on the right posterior of frontoventral kineties; postoral kineties strongly shortened posteriad; terminal fragments consisting of several parallel arranged fragments.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[826,1441,622,705]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis box="[826,976,622,643]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<typeStatus box="[826,878,622,643]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Type</typeStatus>
species:
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Deroux, 1976)" authorityName="Pan &amp; Lin &amp; Gong &amp; Al-Rashied &amp; Song" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Deroux" baseAuthorityYear="1976" box="[990,1441,622,644]" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Hartmannulidae" genus="Aporthotrochilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="pulex" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[990,1252,622,643]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Aporthotrochilia pulex</emphasis>
(Deroux, 1976)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[826,951,652,674]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(basionym: 
<taxonomicName authority="Deroux, 1976" authorityName="Deroux" authorityYear="1976" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Hartmannulidae" genus="Trichopodiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="pulex">
<emphasis box="[1101,1338,652,673]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Trichopodiella pulex</emphasis>
Deroux, 1976
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[826,1441,747,830]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis box="[826,952,747,768]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Etymology:</emphasis>
Composite of Greek prefix apo- (derived from) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Song" authorityYear="2003" box="[1161,1324,777,798]" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Aegyrianidae" genus="Orthotrochilia" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Dysteriida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1161,1324,777,798]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Orthotrochilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; feminine gender.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[826,1442,872,1322]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis box="[826,971,872,893]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Comparison:</emphasis>
In general, 
<taxonomicName authority="Pan &amp; Lin &amp; Gong &amp; Al-Rashied &amp; Song, 2012" authorityName="Pan &amp; Lin &amp; Gong &amp; Al-Rashied &amp; Song" authorityYear="2012" box="[1132,1319,872,893]" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Hartmannulidae" genus="Aporthotrochilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1132,1319,872,893]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Aporthotrochilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1334,1442,872,893]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Song, 2003" authorityName="Song" authorityYear="2003" box="[950,1249,902,923]" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Aegyrianidae" genus="Orthotrochilia" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Dysteriida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[950,1113,902,923]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Orthotrochilia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Song W" box="[1122,1249,902,923]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="169 - 177" refId="ref11208" refString="Song W. 2003. On two marine cyrtophorid ciliates from China, with description of Chlamydonella derouxi nov. spec. and Orthotrochilia pilula (Deroux, 1976) nov. comb., and reestablishment of the genus Orthotrochilia nov. gen. (Protozoa, Ciliophora, Cyrtophorida). Hydrobiologia 499: 169 - 177." type="journal article" year="2003">
Song, 
<quantity box="[1194,1249,902,923]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.087619999999999" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="in" value="2003.0">2003</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in oral ciliature and the pattern of postoral kineties. However, the new genus can be distinguished by the presence of several extra kinetal fragments, i.e. the posterior fragments are on right posterior of frontoventral kineties and the higher number of terminal fragments (more than one vs. single) (
<bibRefCitation author="Song W" box="[1149,1281,1086,1108]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="169 - 177" refId="ref11208" refString="Song W. 2003. On two marine cyrtophorid ciliates from China, with description of Chlamydonella derouxi nov. spec. and Orthotrochilia pilula (Deroux, 1976) nov. comb., and reestablishment of the genus Orthotrochilia nov. gen. (Protozoa, Ciliophora, Cyrtophorida). Hydrobiologia 499: 169 - 177." type="journal article" year="2003">Song, 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[826,1442,872,1322]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Compared with other closely related genera (e.g. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deroux" authorityYear="1976" box="[826,963,1148,1169]" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Hartmannulidae" genus="Microxysma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[826,963,1148,1169]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Microxysma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[975,1121,1147,1168]" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Trochiliidae" genus="Trochilioides" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[975,1121,1147,1168]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Trochilioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deroux" authorityYear="1976" box="[1133,1289,1147,1168]" class="Ciliophora (awaiting allocation)" family="Ciliophora (awaiting allocation)" genus="Chlamydonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Ciliophora (awaiting allocation)" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1133,1289,1147,1168]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Chlamydonyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pan &amp; Lin &amp; Gong &amp; Al-Rashied &amp; Song" authorityYear="2012" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Hartmannulidae" genus="Aporthotrochilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Aporthotrochilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be clearly identified by having two perioral kineties (vs. two circumoral and one preoral kineties), several terminal fragments (vs. single), and several extra kinety fragments caudally positioned on right of frontoventral kineties (vs. none) (
<bibRefCitation author="Deroux G" box="[1211,1379,1300,1322]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="505 - 538" refId="ref9141" refString="Deroux G. 1976 c. Plan cortical des Cyrtophorida. III. - Les structures differenciatrices chez les Dysteriina. Protistologica 12: 505 - 538." type="journal article" year="1976">Deroux, 1976c</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
